parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Phantom Braking due to Faulty Automatic Emergency Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected braking of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if there are vehicles behind the affected car. This issue can also lead to a loss of control, rear-end collisions, or other accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes or decelerates without warning
often with no obstacles or vehicles in front of it. The dashboard may display a "BRAKE" warning light
and the brakes may apply forcefully
even when there is no apparent danger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brake noise and failure can lead to a loss of braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise from the rear brakes
especially when reversing; brakes may not respond or fail to engage; error lights on the dashboard related to the brakes
forward collision warning
and emergency braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure can cause a loss of braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brakes may not respond or fail to engage; error lights on the dashboard related to the brakes
forward collision warning
and emergency braking; abnormal
rattling
or screeching sounds from the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the automatic braking system can increase the risk of rear-end collisions and accidents.
symptoms: Automatic braking system activates at random times
even when there is no obstacle or hazard present; near-miss rear-end collisions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Random Traction Control Light and Feature Disablement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random activation of the traction control light can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses. The disablement of features like economy and cruise control can also affect vehicle performance and safety.
symptoms: The traction control light turns on randomly
accompanied by multiple indicator lights; the vehicle makes an electrical sound; and features like economy and cruise control are disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Loss of Acceleration and Limp Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of acceleration can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses. The activation of limp mode can also leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light begins blinking
the vehicle loses acceleration
and the vehicle drops to a low speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
even when the cruise control is turned off; the vehicle fails to respond to shifting into neutral; and the brakes may not respond as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Overly Sensitive and Erratic Collision Mitigation Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overly sensitive and erratic collision mitigation braking system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The system applies heavy stopping power in unexpected situations
including on the freeway at high speeds; and the system can cause unexpected and abrupt loss of speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unpredictable Cruise Control and Acceleration Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unpredictable cruise control and acceleration issues can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly while using cruise control; and the vehicle may fail to respond to braking or shifting.
